  "name": "Sneak Attack",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-poison-dripping-green.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Beginning at 1st level, you know how to strike subtly and exploit a foe's distraction. Once per turn, you can deal an extra <strong>1d6</strong> damage to one creature you hit with an attack if you have <strong>advantage </strong>on the attack roll. The attack must use a finesse or a ranged weapon.</p>\n<p>You don't need advantage on the attack roll if another enemy of the target is within 5 feet of it, that enemy isn't incapacitated, and you don't have <strong>disadvantage </strong>on the attack roll.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: Shift-click the roll card to roll crit damage.</em></p>\n</section>",
